HEADWORD: Capo tasto
<hw>Ca"po tas"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It.
<ets>capotasto</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Music)</fld> <def>A sort of bar or
movable nut, attached to the finger board of a guitar or other fretted
instrument for the purpose of raising uniformly the pitch of all the
strings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capote</ent>⟦br⟧
